TestNG -- open source, Free
Adding TestNG jar files
--right click on properties--javabuildpath--add library--TestNG--next--finish--open Testng--apply--ok

--Java uint testing framework

install testNG in Eclipse
http://beust.com/eclipse--go to help and paste this URL and search(contact all updates)finish--restart Eclipse

We don't need any main method to execute our class..it will execute all the test cases directly


Annotations:
--@Test--u can right 'n' number of test cases
--With each and every annotation , it should be associated with a method
--3 sections in TestNG are: 1.Pre conditions 2.@Test 3.Post conditions
